<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1882-03-07T23:59:59-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1882-03-07T00:00:00-05:00" n="112" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d112">
                    <head>No. 112.<lb/><hi rend="italic">Mr. <persName type="from">Lowell</persName>
                            to Mr. <persName type="to">Frelinghuysen</persName></hi>.</head>
                    <opener><seg rendition="#center">[Telegram.]</seg></opener>
                    <opener><dateline rendition="#right"><placeName><hi rend="smallcaps">Legation of
                                    the United States</hi>,<lb/><hi rend="italic">London</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1882-03-07"><hi rend="italic">March</hi> 7,
                            1882</date>.</dateline></opener>
                    <p>[Mr. Lowell reports that the instructions in Mr. Frelinghuysen’s dispatch of
                        March 4, 1882, have been obeyed, and that Earl Granville has informed him
                        that the matter will have immediate attention.]</p>
                </div>
                </body></text></TEI>